"""tauceti — the Tau Ceti worker, one self-contained tool.

Consolidates the former loop.sh + round.sh into a single program. Bare `tauceti`
opens a TUI overview + launcher; `tauceti work [--loop]` does the work (one round,
or the driver loop); `tauceti status` prints the read-only survey.

The worker maintains FormalFrontier/TauCeti as `kim-em`: each round does exactly ONE
unit of work, chosen in priority order — merge/abandon/dedup housekeeping (always),
then rebase → review → fix → fix-ci → bump → roadmap. CI-side review and auto-merge
are intentionally off, so the worker is the only path that lands or retires PRs.

Kept as standalone shell on PATH (invoked BY the agents inside a round): claim.sh,
git-safe-push, gh-safe-pr-create. Prompts live in prompts/*.md. External tools we
call: gh, git, uvx tauceti-review, bubble, the agent CLIs (claude/codex/pi).
"""
